  "dateModified": "2026-04-30",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-30",
  "description": "Accentual-syllabic verse is the metrical system that counts both the number of syllables in a line and the placement of stresses among them. A line is built from a fixed number of feet, each foot a small repeating unit (the iamb, the trochee, the anapest, the dactyl) with a prescribed stress pattern. The line is named by combining the foot with the count: iambic pentameter is five iambs, trochaic tetrameter is four trochees, anapestic trimeter is three anapests.\n",
  "name": "Accentual-Syllabic Verse",
